    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="1057"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1057">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3593b.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 14, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>You will communicate the Department’s telegram sent you April 14, 3 p.m., to the
                    Consulates General at Mexico City and Monterey for repetition, merely for their
                    information, to all consular officers under their respective supervisions. Add
                    that the Consults at Chihuahua <pb facs="0905" n="789" xml:id="pg_789"/> and
                    Juárez have already been informed, and the former was further instructed as
                    follows [see telegram April 14, 1912, 3 p.m., supra.].</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
